'''Japanese'''

Meaning 'you'.

There are many forms of 'you' in Japanese and this form is a rude form. Also used between enemies. Usually said by a male Japanese when he is angry.

1.A drill sergeant addressing his grunt.
"貴様はその後では休まれるのはと思うか？"
Kisama wa sono ato de yasumareru no wa to omou ka?!
Lit: You this afterwards can rest you think?!
Meaning: Do you think you can rest after this?!

2.Boxer A talking to Boxer B
"貴様は俺を倒せると思うか？"
Kisama wa ore wo taoseru to omou ka?
Lit: You me can defeat you think?
Meaning: Do you think you can defeat me?

Compare てめえ temē